In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation declaring May 2020 as Jewish American Heritage Month. He acknowledges the contributions of Jewish Americans to the culture and character of the United States in various fields such as arts, sciences, business, and public service. The President also recognizes the resilience of the Jewish people throughout history, despite facing discrimination and violence. He condemns anti-Semitic acts and expresses his commitment to combatting such bigotry. The proclamation calls upon Americans to celebrate the heritage and contributions of American Jews through appropriate programs and activities.